{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1024,"text":"I want you to take a look at this baby."},{"time":4179,"text":"What you're drawn to are her eyes\nand the skin you love to touch."},{"time":9386,"text":"But today I'm going to talk to you\nabout something you can't see."},{"time":12550,"text":"What's going on\nup in that little brain of hers."},{"time":16135,"text":"The modern tools of neuroscience\nare demonstrating to us"},{"time":20080,"text":"that what's going on up there\nis nothing short of rocket science."},{"time":24736,"text":"And what we're learning\nis going to shed some light"},{"time":28197,"text":"on what the romantic writers and poets\ndescribed as the \"celestial openness\""},{"time":34119,"text":"of the child's mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37013,"text":"What we see here is a mother in India,"},{"time":40495,"text":"and she's speaking Koro,\nwhich is a newly discovered language."},{"time":44797,"text":"And she's talking to her baby."},{"time":47089,"text":"What this mother --"},{"time":48269,"text":"and the 800 people who speak\nKoro in the world --"},{"time":51512,"text":"understands is that,\nto preserve this language,"},{"time":54746,"text":"they need to speak it to the babies."},{"time":57356,"text":"And therein lies a critical puzzle."},{"time":60255,"text":"Why is it that you can't\npreserve a language"},{"time":62529,"text":"by speaking to you and I, to the adults?"},{"time":65788,"text":"Well, it's got to do with your brain."},{"time":68538,"text":"What we see here is that language\nhas a critical period for learning."},{"time":73000,"text":"The way to read this slide is to look\nat your age on the horizontal axis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76824,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":79531,"text":"And you'll see on the vertical\nyour skill at acquiring a second language."},{"time":83789,"text":"The babies and children are geniuses\nuntil they turn seven,"},{"time":87672,"text":"and then there's a systematic decline."},{"time":90000,"text":"After puberty, we fall off the map."},{"time":92934,"text":"No scientists dispute this curve,"},{"time":95490,"text":"but laboratories all over the world"},{"time":97469,"text":"are trying to figure out\nwhy it works this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100518,"text":"Work in my lab is focused on the first\ncritical period in development,"},{"time":104576,"text":"and that is the period in which babies"},{"time":106445,"text":"try to master which sounds\nare used in their language."},{"time":109834,"text":"We think, by studying\nhow the sounds are learned,"},{"time":112348,"text":"we'll have a model\nfor the rest of language,"},{"time":114637,"text":"and perhaps for critical periods\nthat may exist in childhood"},{"time":117599,"text":"for social, emotional\nand cognitive development."},{"time":121035,"text":"So we've been studying the babies"},{"time":123000,"text":"using a technique\nthat we're using all over the world"},{"time":125527,"text":"and the sounds of all languages."},{"time":127407,"text":"The baby sits on a parent's lap,"},{"time":129222,"text":"and we train them to turn\ntheir heads when a sound changes --"},{"time":132167,"text":"like from \"ah\" to \"ee.\""},{"time":133649,"text":"If they do so at the appropriate time,\nthe black box lights up"},{"time":137106,"text":"and a panda bear pounds a drum."},{"time":139114,"text":"A six-monther adores the task."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142160,"text":"What have we learned?"},{"time":143345,"text":"Well, babies all over the world"},{"time":145529,"text":"are what I like to describe\nas \"citizens of the world.\""},{"time":149646,"text":"They can discriminate\nall the sounds of all languages,"},{"time":152598,"text":"no matter what country we're testing\nand what language we're using,"},{"time":155854,"text":"and that's remarkable\nbecause you and I can't do that."},{"time":158873,"text":"We're culture-bound listeners."},{"time":160868,"text":"We can discriminate the sounds\nof our own language,"},{"time":163287,"text":"but not those of foreign languages."},{"time":165158,"text":"So the question arises:\nWhen do those citizens of the world"},{"time":168349,"text":"turn into the language-bound\nlisteners that we are?"},{"time":171257,"text":"And the answer:\nbefore their first birthdays."},{"time":174418,"text":"What you see here is performance\non that head-turn task"},{"time":177574,"text":"for babies tested in Tokyo\nand the United States,"},{"time":180061,"text":"here in Seattle,"},{"time":181523,"text":"as they listened to \"ra\" and \"la\" --"},{"time":183296,"text":"sounds important to English,\nbut not to Japanese."},{"time":186126,"text":"So at six to eight months,\nthe babies are totally equivalent."},{"time":189528,"text":"Two months later,\nsomething incredible occurs."},{"time":192106,"text":"The babies in the United States\nare getting a lot better,"},{"time":194810,"text":"babies in Japan are getting a lot worse,"},{"time":196758,"text":"but both of those groups of babies\nare preparing for exactly the language"},{"time":200232,"text":"that they are going to learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201748,"text":"So the question is: What's happening\nduring this critical two-month period?"},{"time":206396,"text":"This is the critical period\nfor sound development,"},{"time":208763,"text":"but what's going on up there?"},{"time":210202,"text":"So there are two things going on."},{"time":212205,"text":"The first is that the babies\nare listening intently to us,"},{"time":215105,"text":"and they're taking statistics\nas they listen to us talk --"},{"time":218862,"text":"they're taking statistics."},{"time":220867,"text":"So listen to two mothers\nspeaking motherese --"},{"time":223430,"text":"the universal language\nwe use when we talk to kids --"},{"time":226496,"text":"first in English and then in Japanese."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228731,"text":"(Video) Ah, I love your big blue eyes --"},{"time":232194,"text":"so pretty and nice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236049,"text":"(Japanese)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":242452,"text":"Patricia Kuhl: During the production\nof speech, when babies listen,"},{"time":245843,"text":"what they're doing is taking statistics\non the language that they hear."},{"time":251353,"text":"And those distributions grow."},{"time":254287,"text":"And what we've learned is that babies\nare sensitive to the statistics,"},{"time":258684,"text":"and the statistics of Japanese\nand English are very, very different."},{"time":262536,"text":"English has a lot of Rs and Ls."},{"time":265217,"text":"The distribution shows."},{"time":267000,"text":"And the distribution of Japanese\nis totally different,"},{"time":269864,"text":"where we see a group\nof intermediate sounds,"},{"time":272889,"text":"which is known as the Japanese \"R.\""},{"time":275328,"text":"So babies absorb\nthe statistics of the language"},{"time":279460,"text":"and it changes their brains;"},{"time":281162,"text":"it changes them\nfrom the citizens of the world"},{"time":283337,"text":"to the culture-bound\nlisteners that we are."},{"time":286307,"text":"But we as adults are no longer\nabsorbing those statistics."},{"time":291044,"text":"We are governed\nby the representations in memory"},{"time":293625,"text":"that were formed early in development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296198,"text":"So what we're seeing here"},{"time":298000,"text":"is changing our models\nof what the critical period is about."},{"time":301257,"text":"We're arguing from\na mathematical standpoint"},{"time":304050,"text":"that the learning of language\nmaterial may slow down"},{"time":307214,"text":"when our distributions stabilize."},{"time":309618,"text":"It's raising lots of questions\nabout bilingual people."},{"time":312918,"text":"Bilinguals must keep two sets\nof statistics in mind at once"},{"time":316973,"text":"and flip between them,\none after the other,"},{"time":319880,"text":"depending on who they're speaking to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321676,"text":"So we asked ourselves,"},{"time":322854,"text":"can the babies take statistics\non a brand new language?"},{"time":326285,"text":"And we tested this\nby exposing American babies"},{"time":329587,"text":"who'd never heard a second language"},{"time":331300,"text":"to Mandarin for the first time\nduring the critical period."},{"time":334040,"text":"We knew that, when monolinguals\nwere tested in Taipei and Seattle"},{"time":337601,"text":"on the Mandarin sounds,\nthey showed the same pattern."},{"time":340287,"text":"Six to eight months,\nthey're totally equivalent."},{"time":342782,"text":"Two months later,\nsomething incredible happens."},{"time":345342,"text":"But the Taiwanese babies are getting\nbetter, not the American babies."},{"time":348918,"text":"What we did was expose American babies,\nduring this period, to Mandarin."},{"time":353824,"text":"It was like having Mandarin relatives\ncome and visit for a month"},{"time":356856,"text":"and move into your house\nand talk to the babies for 12 sessions."},{"time":360677,"text":"Here's what it looked like\nin the laboratory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362907,"text":"(Mandarin)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384662,"text":"PK: So what have we done\nto their little brains?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":386932,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"We had to run a control group to make sure"},{"time":391695,"text":"that coming into the laboratory\ndidn't improve your Mandarin skills."},{"time":394931,"text":"So a group of babies came in\nand listened to English."},{"time":397608,"text":"And we can see from the graph"},{"time":399034,"text":"that exposure to English\ndidn't improve their Mandarin."},{"time":401641,"text":"But look at what happened to the babies\nexposed to Mandarin for 12 sessions."},{"time":405260,"text":"They were as good as the babies in Taiwan"},{"time":407684,"text":"who'd been listening\nfor 10 and a half months."},{"time":410684,"text":"What it demonstrated is that babies\ntake statistics on a new language."},{"time":414532,"text":"Whatever you put in front of them,\nthey'll take statistics on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"But we wondered what role"},{"time":419614,"text":"the human being played\nin this learning exercise."},{"time":424168,"text":"So we ran another group of babies\nin which the kids got the same dosage,"},{"time":428508,"text":"the same 12 sessions,\nbut over a television set."},{"time":431000,"text":"And another group of babies\nwho had just audio exposure"},{"time":434685,"text":"and looked at a teddy bear on the screen."},{"time":436797,"text":"What did we do to their brains?"},{"time":439000,"text":"What you see here is the audio result --"},{"time":442923,"text":"no learning whatsoever --"},{"time":444685,"text":"and the video result --"},{"time":447236,"text":"no learning whatsoever."},{"time":449105,"text":"It takes a human being\nfor babies to take their statistics."},{"time":453622,"text":"The social brain is controlling"},{"time":455812,"text":"when the babies\nare taking their statistics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457941,"text":"We want to get inside the brain\nand see this thing happening"},{"time":461458,"text":"as babies are in front of televisions,\nas opposed to in front of human beings."},{"time":465420,"text":"Thankfully, we have a new machine,\nmagnetoencephalography,"},{"time":470141,"text":"that allows us to do this."},{"time":471458,"text":"It looks like a hair dryer from Mars."},{"time":474067,"text":"But it's completely safe,\ncompletely noninvasive and silent."},{"time":478574,"text":"We're looking at millimeter accuracy"},{"time":481041,"text":"with regard to spatial\nand millisecond accuracy"},{"time":484381,"text":"using 306 SQUIDs --"},{"time":487027,"text":"these are superconducting\nquantum interference devices --"},{"time":490151,"text":"to pick up the magnetic fields\nthat change as we do our thinking."},{"time":494249,"text":"We're the first in the world\nto record babies in an MEG machine"},{"time":499882,"text":"while they are learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502297,"text":"So this is little Emma."},{"time":504000,"text":"She's a six-monther."},{"time":505932,"text":"And she's listening to various languages\nin the earphones that are in her ears."},{"time":511074,"text":"You can see, she can move around."},{"time":513322,"text":"We're tracking her head\nwith little pellets in a cap,"},{"time":517116,"text":"so she's free to move\ncompletely unconstrained."},{"time":520115,"text":"It's a technical tour de force."},{"time":522352,"text":"What are we seeing?"},{"time":523960,"text":"We're seeing the baby brain."},{"time":525878,"text":"As the baby hears a word in her language,\nthe auditory areas light up,"},{"time":531188,"text":"and then subsequently areas surrounding it\nthat we think are related to coherence,"},{"time":536000,"text":"getting the brain coordinated\nwith its different areas, and causality,"},{"time":540000,"text":"one brain area\ncausing another to activate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543601,"text":"We are embarking on a grand\nand golden age of knowledge"},{"time":549009,"text":"about child's brain development."},{"time":551269,"text":"We're going to be able\nto see a child's brain"},{"time":553714,"text":"as they experience an emotion,\nas they learn to speak and read,"},{"time":557979,"text":"as they solve a math problem,\nas they have an idea."},{"time":561515,"text":"And we're going to be able to invent\nbrain-based interventions"},{"time":564888,"text":"for children who have difficulty learning."},{"time":567571,"text":"Just as the poets and writers described,"},{"time":570661,"text":"we're going to be able to see, I think,\nthat wondrous openness,"},{"time":574839,"text":"utter and complete openness,\nof the mind of a child."},{"time":579024,"text":"In investigating the child's brain,"},{"time":581724,"text":"we're going to uncover deep truths\nabout what it means to be human,"},{"time":585744,"text":"and in the process,"},{"time":586923,"text":"we may be able to help keep\nour own minds open to learning"},{"time":590018,"text":"for our entire lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591733,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}